      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#substrate-anchored",
        "dcterms:title": "The WHOLE Hologram OS and every app are anchored on the unified UOR substrate (the deferred σ-axis convergence, ADR-026/holospaces CC-51) — not a locally-served image but a set of objects on the shared content-addressed network. Every object — every entry in the OS-wide κ-route closure AND every entry in every app's lock closure — is DUAL-AXIS: it carries its OS serving key (did:holo:sha256) AND its unified-substrate σ-axis κ (a did:holo:blake3 alsoKnownAs alias = BLAKE3 over the canonical form, byte-identical to hologram's kappa()). The κ-route resolves any object by EITHER axis at /.holo/<axis>/<hex>, re-derived and refused on mismatch (Law L5) — dev (holo-serve-fhs) and prod (the content-verify Service Worker holo-fhs-sw.js) identically (Law L2). So an OS or app object resolves on any substrate peer by its content address. BLAKE3≡kappa() is grounded in the external σ-axis KAT oracle (holo-blake3 row, never self-reference); the few apps with un-vendored binary bundles are reported, not silently passed."
      },
