      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#corpus-addressed",
        "dcterms:title": "EVERY first-party file in Hologram OS2 + Hologram Apps is a first-class, attribute-addressed object native to the unified UOR substrate — not only the served runtime + app closures, but the WHOLE corpus (the OS image, the build/witness tools, the native host, the docs, every app). The substrate object index (os/etc/substrate-index.json) gives each file its DUAL-AXIS content address — did:holo:sha256 (OS serving) ⊕ did:holo:blake3 (the substrate σ-axis ≡ hologram's kappa()) — so identity is the content, never the path (Law L1), and every object re-derives (Law L5). Consume-by-reference (ADR-006): external/regenerable trees (.git · node_modules · Rust target · the holospaces substrate submodule, whose identity is upstream) are excluded, not re-minted; transient runtime artifacts (logs · progress · witness outputs) are not canonical forms and are not indexed. The index is deterministic (sorted, no timestamps) so it re-derives byte-for-byte. A concurrently-generating process (a live model-compile) is reported as drift, not hidden."
      },
      "earl:result": {
