      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#substrate-oracle",
        "dcterms:title": "Interop EXERCISED against the LIVE hologram substrate, not a reimplementation: the substrate's OWN compiled kappa() (the holospaces_web wasm — the real code peers run) independently derives the SAME σ-axis κ that Hologram OS minted and recorded for REAL objects (the canonical shell, the σ-axis primitive, the Files app, a just-sealed vendored bundle). So every OS/app object resolves + verifies on a real substrate peer by its content address (the declared did:holo:blake3 alias IS the substrate's live derivation). Offline (no wasm), the authority is the KAT-pinned holo-blake3 row."
      },
