        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-link",
        "dcterms:title": "CLOSURE — content-addressed composition (Holo Link, ADR-0060): every module is a self-verifying WASM κ-object that imports others BY CONTENT ADDRESS (the κ is the WASM import's module-name, so a module's own bytes commit to its dependencies); running LINKS the dependency graph from the store — verified by re-derivation (Law L5), instantiated once (Law L3) — so objects combine into new self-verifying objects and split back apart, connected only by a single self-referential κ. A tampered dependency refuses the whole run. Build·Run·Share becomes Build·Compose·Run·Share over a universe of interoperable serverless apps; the lean substitute for a 100 MB compiler toolchain (WASM is the universal IR, already in every browser — ship a linker, not a compiler)"
      },
