      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-ux",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo UX is the single canonical, self-verifying source of the EXPERIENCE (ADR-0062) — the experience analogue of Holo UI's token contract. The system autodetects the host OS (Windows · macOS · iOS · iPadOS · Android · ChromeOS · Linux) and adapts its native feel dynamically — modifier key, window-control side, font, accent, shortcuts (holo-platform.js → data-holo-platform, seeded without overriding the user) — so it feels familiar and effortless on every machine. Thirteen tenets (the five founding principles + Steve Jobs's eight UX lessons) are each a checkable obligation; capability tier, plain voice and a tier-aware resource budget (time · attention · compute · memory · energy held sacred, interaction ≤100ms / RAIL) are resolved, not guessed. The canonical parameters are sealed as ONE UOR object (etc/holo-ux/doctrine.uor.json) that re-derives to its content address and whose source links re-derive (Law L5) — every holospace binds the κ rather than re-implementing UX"
      },
