        "dcterms:title": "Hologram OS"
      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-pm",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Product Manager is the canonical full-cycle product-management framework for Hologram-native products + applications (ADR-0066) — the bridge that turns ideas into scalable, enterprise-grade products that solve real pain points. It STRICTLY adopts the Pragmatic Framework (pragmaticinstitute.com/product/framework) VERBATIM — 37 activities ('boxes') in 7 categories (Market · Focus · Business · Planning · Programs · Enablement · Support), on the strategic→tactical axis, a clear path from a great idea to a great product — and WIRES every activity Hologram realizes to the tool that executes it (User Personas → Holo UX capability tiers · Use Scenarios/Stakeholder Comm → the plain voice · Requirements/Roadmap/Positioning → Holo Product · Buyer Experience → Holo UX · Launch/Awareness/Advocacy → Holo Share-to-Run · Pricing/Revenue/Profitability → Holo Own·Settle · Buy-Build-Partner/Innovation → Holo App build·compose · Measurement → the witnessed gate · Operations → the conscience gate · Content/Sales Tools → the Holo SDK + scaffolder), so the framework is EXECUTED on the substrate, not just described; the market/business judgment boxes stay the PM's job (NIHITO — no tool can own them). It is sealed as ONE self-verifying UOR object (etc/holo-pm/pm.uor.json) that re-derives to its content address and Merkle-links the Holo Product foundation it manages + every wired tool (Law L5); it is surfaced as the canonical PANE (holo-pm.html) and exposed through the Holo SDK (pm()), to deliver one seamless, unified, coordinated PM framework"
      },
