        "dcterms:title": "Hologram OS"
      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-q-spine",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Q is a substrate-native chat app (LibreChat-parity spine, reimplemented natively): conversations persist as content-addressed κ-objects — NOT a database — the parentMessageId branch tree is a verify-on-load Merkle-DAG (every message links its parent's κ; regenerate/edit = a new sibling κ; fork = a new conversation referencing the SAME κ-objects, O(1), zero copy), and every answer is a re-derivable PROV-O inference receipt sealed to its own did:holo. Tampering one byte of any message or receipt is refused by re-derivation; identical (context ⊕ prompt ⊕ model ⊕ params) replays from the κ-memo in O(1) with no decode"
      },
      "earl:result": {
