      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "earl:Assertion",
      "earl:assertedBy": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/tools/gate"
      },
      "earl:subject": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os",
        "dcterms:title": "Hologram OS"
      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#qvac-sdk",
        "dcterms:title": "The QVAC SDK (docs.qvac.tether.io) is encoded NATIVE to Hologram OS (ADR-0067) — Tether's local AI SDK as one self-verifying contract on the substrate, so a builder writes QVAC code and it just runs: beautiful, fast, lean, serverless. It encodes the WHOLE QVAC surface — the 13 AI capabilities (text generation · embeddings · RAG · translation · classification · multimodal · image · video · transcription · text-to-speech · voice assistant · VLA · OCR · fine-tuning), the model lifecycle (a model is a content-addressed κ-disk, so loading verifies it), the runtime (cancel · suspend · resume · state · logging · profiler), P2P delegation and the OpenAI-compatible server — and SATISFIES it on the substrate: every capability call passes the fail-closed conscience gate (ADR-033), runs over the browser-native engine (a deterministic reference brain that ALWAYS runs with no download now; Holo Q / QVAC WebGPU, ADR-0052, when a model is bound), and seals a re-derivable PROV-O inference receipt — so local inference is PROVABLE, not just asserted (identical inputs replay the same κ; a tampered output is refused). The witness RUNS the shipped runtime façade in Node (a real completion streams tokens and its receipt re-derives; embeddings/RAG/classify are deterministic). Serverless: the OpenAI /v1 routes are answered by a Service-Worker fetch handler, no process, no port (Law L1/L4). Operative: the Holo SDK exposes qvac() and the scaffolder builds QVAC apps on the contract (builtOn qvac-sdk + @hologram/qvac + conformsTo the ns), so any builder ships an on-device AI holospace in one command. Encoded — not vendored — under the holospaces Laws; honest where weights are absent (the call reports the missing model, never fakes output)"
      },
      "earl:result": {
        "@type": "earl:TestResult",
        "earl:outcome": {
          "@id": "earl:failed"
        }
